==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Morose
<hw>Mo*rose"</hw> <pr>(m⟦osl⟧*r⟦omac⟧s")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>morosus</ets>, prop., excessively addicted to any particular way or
habit, fr. <ets>mos</ets>, <ets>moris</ets>, manner, habit, way of life:
cf. F. <ets>morose</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of a sour temper;
sullen and austere; ill-humored; severe.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>morose</xex> and affected taciturnity.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>I.
Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lascivious; brooding over evil thoughts.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sullen; gruff; severe; austere; gloomy; crabbed;
crusty; churlish; surly; ill-humored.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morosely</ent>⟦br⟧
